fields.description:
So very trivial, but it just _bugs_ me that on profile pages the username title is offset.. (as attached).

Found in a cursory check that setting <h1> to:

{code}
#!
display: inline-block
{code}

Snapped it back into place.

Currently, if you are over your plan limit, you may not see any warning on the bitbucket site. We are working to fix this asap. This issue is to help those encountering errors when pushing like

{code}
#!bash
fatal: https://user@bitbucket.org/team/repo.git/info/refs not valid: is this a git repository?
{code}

To resolve this issue, visit your plans and billing page and remove/verify the number of users with some level of access to your repositories. This can be found at:

{code}
#!bash
https://bitbucket.org/account/user/USERNAME/plans-and-billing/
{code}
